omic environment, localization strategies, and spatial distribution, creating a new network structure with new catchment and commuting links. It has also been associated with the development of large retail units and a fundamental change in shopping behaviour and consumer preferences of the affected populations by restricting purposeful shopping only and moving to entertainment and leisure in shopping centres. The book also reflects current trends in the use of smart technologies in shopping and responds to the impact of the Covid-19 pandemic on today's retail.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aretailing, retail structure, shopping centres, challenges, globalisation, Central Europe.1 aBilková, Kristína, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBilková, Kristína, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIlnicki, Dariusz, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aIlnicki, Dariusz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrižan, František, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKrižan, František, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKunc, Josef, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNovotná, Markéta, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aNovotná, Markéta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSikos T., Tamás, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSikos, Tamás T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWyeth, Ryan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rel